text: Norrmalm is a borough (stadsdelsområde) in central Stockholm, Sweden. It is named after the dominating district. ==Overview== Except Norrmalm (proper) there are two districts in the borough: Skeppsholmen and Vasastaden. A portion of northern Östermalm is also organized in Norrmalm borough. The population is 61,905 on an area of 4.95 km², which gives a density of 12,506.06/km². The most populous district is Vasastaden. ==References== ==External links== Category:Boroughs of Stockholm
